r of Crestwood Heights, a defining work of postwar social science. He led an ambitious mental health project in Canadian schools, and was a founding father of York University. However, Seeley's struggle with mental illness and Jewish identity brought him into conflict with the Canadian establishment. His career ended in academic exile, but his dream of a mental health revolution still resonates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aJewszCanadavBiography. 0aJewszCanadaxIdentity. 0aSocial reformersxMental healthvBiography. 0aSocial reformerszCanadavBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Social Scientists & Psychologists.2bisacsh  a1950s.  a1960s.  aCanadian Education.  aCanadian Jewish history.  aCanadian Jews.  aCanadian social science.  aEducation.  aEugenics.  aHistoriography.  aHome Children.  aJewish History.  aJohn R Friedeberg Seeley.  aMental Health Movement.  aMental Health.  aPop Sociologist.  aPsychoanalysis.  aSociology.  aSuicide in the Military.  aToronto Star.  aacademic biographies.  aanti-Semitism.  aantisemitism in Canada.  aantisemitism.  asocial science.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package 2019z978311068819108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644690512zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644690512423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cove